      • splitN

        default List<List<SquareRangedList<T>>> splitN(int outer,
                                               int inner,
                                               int num,
                                               boolean randomize)
        Splits equally squares into outer * inner and squares are divided to list of sizes num.
        Parameters:
        outer - the number of split outer range.
        inner - the number ot split inner range.
        num - the number dividing squares to List.
        randomize - if true, splited squares are added in order from begining, else, added in random.
        Returns:
        List of list of SquareRangedList. Size of outer list is numTherads. Size of inner list is number of SquareRangedList for each thread.

      • subView

        SquareRangedList<T> subView(SquareRange range)
        Provides a SquareRangedList of the elements contained in this instance on the specified SquareRange.

        If the provided range exceeds the indices contained in this instance the method will return the elements it contains that fit within the provided range.

        Parameters:
        range - range of indices of which a copy is desired
        Returns:
        a ranged list of the elements contained in this SquareRangedList that fit in the provided range.

      • teamedSplitNM

        default List<List<SquareRangedList<T>>> teamedSplitNM(int outer,
                                                      int inner,
                                                      TeamedPlaceGroup pg,
                                                      int numThreads,
                                                      long seed)
        Splits equally squares into outer * inner and return some squares for each host equally. Assigned squares are divided to list of sizes nThreads.
        Parameters:
        outer - the number of split outer range.
        inner - the number ot split inner range.
        pg - the group between which this ranged list is split
        numThreads - the number of threads to whom squares should be assigned to
        seed - seed used to randomly assign squares to hosts, must the same on all hosts
        Returns:
        List of list of SquareRangedList. Size of outer list is numTherads. Size of inner list is number of SquareRangedList for each thread.
